<span class="header1">BUSINESS & INDUSTRY</span>
<p>If you like to be challenged mentally, you may want to consider
this occupational field. The occupations in this field need people
who are good at solving problems.</p>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Corporate Lawyer</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/CG/1366.jpg"
width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Corporate Lawyer" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>As a corporate lawyer, you would work for a
large company.  You would use your knowledge of the law to advise
executives.  You would tell them how to best protect the company and
stay within the laws that govern business.  You would also gather
and communicate information to other legal professionals or
clients.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>To become a lawyer, you need a bachelor's degree
plus three years of law school.  Lawyers must pass a written test
known as the "bar exam" also.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The median annual wage of corporate lawyers was
$118,160 in May 2016. </blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Management
Consultant</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/CG/1370.jpg"
width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Placement Specialist" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>If you enjoy helping people in practical ways,
you might become a placement specialist (employment recruiter). You
would find job opportunities in the community.  You would then
find people within the community to fill these jobs. You would
interview the person to be hired.  You might also test the person
using an instrument like the Interest Inventory that you
took.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>You need a bachelor's degree for this
job.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The median annual wage of management consultants
was $81,330 in May 2016.
</blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Retail Salesperson</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/CG/1302.jpg"
width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Retail Salesperson" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>When you go into a department store, you may
have someone who comes to you and asks, "May I help you?"  This
person is a retail salesperson. A retail salesperson answers
questions that customers ask and helps the customer decide on what
to buy. He/she also "rings up" the sale on a cash register or
computer. Sometimes he/she is asked to restock shelves or
racks.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>Companies provide on-the-job training for this
job. They may require special knowledge for people who want to work
in technical sales positions.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The median annual wage of retail salespersons
was $22,900 in May 2016. </blockquote>

